  "text": "In addition, the organic removal with single partial heating modules can be 2 compared to other researches even though it is restricted by the low C/N ratio. The 3 total organic carbon utilization of 83.9 % at C/N ratio of 6.5 has been reported 4 [CITATION_1] in previous research. Zhong et al (2013) has found that the 5 organic removal ratio reached 42.2% in case of C/N ratio of 6. These results 6 emphasized that C/N ratio of the substrate is a crucial controlling factor in the 7 anaerobic digestion. 8",
